+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **The Scenario**                                                      |
|                                                                       |
| In Module 4 you identified **eight deliberate security flaws** in     |
| ShopCo\'s Flask source code. Every one was written by a developer. In |
| a well-run Secure Software Development Lifecycle, each flaw would     |
| have been caught **before it reached production.**                    |
|                                                                       |
| Your task: assign each flaw to the **earliest** SSDLC stage that      |
| could have caught it --- and explain how in one sentence.             |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

**Stage Reference Key:**

+-------------+-------------+-------------+-------------+-------------+
| **REQ**     | **CODE**    | **SAST**    | **CFG**     | **DAST**    |
|             |             |             |             |             |
| R           | Secure      | Static      | Config &    | DAST & Pen  |
| equirements | Coding      | Analysis    | Secrets     | Test        |
| & Threat    | Standards & | Tools       | Review      |             |
| Modelling   | Review      | (SAST)      |             |             |
+-------------+-------------+-------------+-------------+-------------+

**Instructions:**

1.  Assign each flaw to the **earliest** SSDLC stage that would have
    caught it. Write REQ / CODE / SAST / CFG / or DAST in the right-hand
    column.

2.  In the same cell, write one sentence explaining **how** that stage
    would have surfaced the flaw.

3.  You have **12 minutes.** Be ready to defend your most controversial
    assignment to the room.

  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **\#**   **Code Location**                **What the Flaw Is** **Earliest SSDLC Stage (REQ
                                                                 / CODE / SAST / CFG /
                                                                 DAST) + one sentence: how
                                                                 would that stage have
                                                                 caught it?**
  -------- -------------------------------- -------------------- ---------------------------
  **1**    app.secret_key = \"password\"    Hardcoded, trivial   
                                            secret key in source 
                                            code                 

  **2**    app.config\[\"DEBUG\"\] = True   Debug mode enabled   
                                            --- could reach      
                                            production           

  **3**    hashlib.md5(password.encode())   MD5 used for         
                                            password hashing     

  **4**    f\"SELECT\...WHERE               Raw f-string         
           username=\'{username}\'\"        interpolation in SQL 
                                            query                

  **5**    session\[\"user\"\] =            Session stores       
           row\[\"username\"\]              mutable username,    
                                            not user_id          

  **6**    def profile(): (no auth check)   Route has no         
                                            authentication check 
                                            at all               

  **7**    user_id =                        User ID accepted     
           request.args.get(\"user_id\")    from URL --- IDOR    
                                            vector               

  **8**    os.popen(f\"ping -c 2 {host}\")  Unsanitised user     
                                            input passed to      
                                            shell                
  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **Group Discussion Questions**                                        |
|                                                                       |
| 4.  Flaws 1 and 2 are in the first 6 lines. What process or cultural  |
|     pressure causes developers to leave \"temporary\" insecure config |
|     in production code?                                               |
|                                                                       |
| 5.  Flaws 4 and 8 both concatenate user input into a command string.  |
|     What **single principle** prevents both? State it in one          |
|     sentence.                                                         |
|                                                                       |
| 6.  Flaws 6 and 7 combine so an unauthenticated attacker can dump the |
|     whole user table. Which stage catches this first --- and why      |
|     might another group disagree?                                     |
|                                                                       |
| 7.  Flaw 3 (MD5) lives in the database seeder, not a live route. What |
|     does this tell you about the **scope** of security review beyond  |
|     the main application code?                                        |
